    ðŸ”¹ `--format=FORMAT` --> ðŸ’½ Specifies the output image format (e.g., `i386-pc`).
    ðŸ”¹ `--output=FILE` --> ðŸ’¾ Specifies the output file name.
    ðŸ”¹ `--modules=MODULE1,MODULE2,...` --> ðŸ§© Specifies a list of GRUB modules to include in the image. If this option is not used, default modules are included.

ðŸ›  **Examples:**

    $ grub-mkstandalone --output=boot.img --format=i386-pc --directory=/usr/lib/grub/i386-pc

    ðŸ”¹ Creates a GRUB image named `boot.img` in the `i386-pc` format, using GRUB files from `/usr/lib/grub/i386-pc`.

    $ grub-mkstandalone --output=usbboot.img --format=i386-pc --directory=/usr/lib/grub/i386-pc --modules="normal linux ext2"

    ðŸ”¹ Creates a GRUB image named `usbboot.img` that includes the `normal`, `linux`, and `ext2` modules.

